The box <> is a placeholder for something not (yet) fully specified.

== Contexts ==

* In array declaration

 {{Ada/kw|type}} Some_Array {{Ada/kw|is}} (Integer {{Ada/kw|range}} <>) {{Ada/kw|of}} Some_Type;

Declare an array type with bounds known only at runtime.

* a type that has unknown discriminants

 {{Ada/kw|type}} T {{Ada/delimiter|(}}<>{{Ada/delimiter|)}} {{Ada/kw|is}} {{Ada/kw|private}}{{Ada/delimiter|;}}

* Generic declaration of a discrete type

 {{Ada/kw|generic}}
   {{Ada/kw|type}} T {{Ada/kw|is}} (<>);

It means that <tt>T</tt> must be a discrete type: either an enumeration, a
range, or a modular type.

* component association in Ada 2005

 Some_Rec_Type'({{Ada/kw|others}} => <>);

* partial parameterization of generics in Ada 2005

 {{Ada/kw|generic}}
   {{Ada/kw|with}} {{Ada/kw|package}} P {{Ada/keyword|is}} {{Ada/kw|new}} G
      (Param_1 {{Ada/delimiter|1==>}} T{{Ada/delimiter|,}}
       {{Ada/kw|others}} {{Ada/delimiter|1==>}} <>{{Ada/delimiter|)}}{{Ada/delimiter|;}}

