{{Ada/Navigation|Libraries|Web|AWS}}
__TOC__

'''AWS''' is a complete framework to develop [[w:Web application|Web based applications]]. The main part of the framework is the embedded [[w:Web server|web server]]. This small yet powerful Web server can be embedded into your application so your application will be able to talk with a standard Web browser like [[w:Internet Explorer|Microsoft Internet Explorer]] or [[w:Firefox|Firefox]] for example. Around this Web server a lot of services have been developed.

AWS supports '''SOAP''' [[w:Web service|Web Services]].

''See also'': [http://libre.adacore.com/tools/aws/ AWS web site]

== Sample code ==

The famous Hello World demo for AWS, a complete Web server that will display "Hello world!" for every requests made to '''localhost''' on port '''8080'''.

 {{Ada/kw|with}} AWS.Default;
 {{Ada/kw|with}} AWS.Response;
 {{Ada/kw|with}} AWS.Server;
 {{Ada/kw|with}} AWS.Status;

 {{Ada/kw|procedure}} Hello_World {{Ada/kw|is}}

    WS : AWS.Server.HTTP;

    {{Ada/kw|function}} HW_CB (Request : AWS.Status.Data) {{Ada/kw|return}} AWS.Response.Data {{Ada/kw|is}}
    {{Ada/kw|begin}}
       {{Ada/kw|return}} AWS.Response.Build ("text/html", "Hello world !");
    {{Ada/kw|end}} HW_CB;

 {{Ada/kw|begin}}
    AWS.Server.Start (WS, "Hello World", Callback => HW_CB'{{Ada/attribute|Access}});

    {{Ada/kw|delay}} 60.0;

    AWS.Server.Shutdown (WS);
 {{Ada/kw|end}} Hello_World;

